issue.title: lossless-json internals bleed to display
issue.body:
Hello,
While working on json tree display in redis-commander, I noticed that some undesirable data appears in tree. (See pic below, losslessNumber and isLosslessNumber are definitely not mine.)
I suspect it comes from lossless-json. If you are trying to only solve the BigInt issue with JSON, [this solution](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/BigInt#use_within_json) is simple and elegant and does not require a special parser. I noticed you're working on it these days, so it may just be a temporary issue, I just bring it to your attention. You get to this when you're trying to view a tree of a redis string value (not ReJSON), string value that contains valid json, and json that contains numeric values; problem does not exhibit when json has string only values).

Best regards.

issue.title: running after a pip3 install and make init both fail after recent update to fido2 library
issue.body:
The fido2 library has renamed the CTAP1 class to Ctap1 and CTAP2 class to Ctap2, deprecating the old names, and they appear to have removed the old names in the newest version of the fido2 library (currently 1.0.0). 

This causes errors when using "make init" or trying to run the solo1 cli after installing it with pip3, as it will get the latest version of the fido2 library and crash with the following error:

    ImportError: cannot import name 'CTAP1' from 'fido2.ctap1' ([...]/solo1-cli/venv/lib/python3.10/site-packages/fido2/ctap1.py)

Pinning the fido2 package to version 0.9.2 fixes the crash, but probably the solo1-cli code should be updated to match the most recent (and hopefully stable) API of the fido2 library.

By default the action now expects SPDX-compliant licenses everywhere. If you were previously using license names in the allow or deny lists make sure they're valid!

Support for external configuration files

You can now specify a configuration file external to your repository. This allows organizations to have a single configuration file for all their repos.

Broader license support

We've added support for a much broader set of project licenses by using GitHub's Licenses API.

SPDX Compliance

All of our license-related code now expects SPDX-compliant licenses or expressions. This allows us to standardize on a license naming scheme that already supports OR/AND expressions.

Disable individual checks

You can now use the boolean options license-check and vulnerability-check to disable either one of the checks. More information in our configuration options.

Hello,
While working on json tree display in redis-commander, I noticed that some undesirable data appears in tree. (See pic below, losslessNumber and isLosslessNumber are definitely not mine.)
I suspect it comes from lossless-json. If you are trying to only solve the BigInt issue with JSON, [this solution](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/BigInt#use_within_json) is simple and elegant and does not require a special parser. issue.title: running after a pip3 install and make init both fail after recent update to fido2 library
issue.body:
The fido2 library has renamed the CTAP1 class to Ctap1 and CTAP2 class to Ctap2, deprecating the old names, and they appear to have removed the old names in the newest version of the fido2 library (currently 1.0.0). 

This causes errors when using "make init" or trying to run the solo1 cli after installing it with pip3, as it will get the latest version of the fido2 library and crash with the following error:

    ImportError: cannot import name 'CTAP1' from 'fido2.ctap1' ([...]/solo1-cli/venv/lib/python3.10/site-packages/fido2/ctap1.py)

Pinning the fido2 package to version 0.9.2 fixes the crash, but probably the solo1-cli code should be updated to match the most recent (and hopefully stable) API of the fido2 library.

issue.title: running after a pip3 install and make init both fail after recent update to fido2 library
issue.body:
The fido2 library has renamed the CTAP1 class to Ctap1 and CTAP2 class to Ctap2, deprecating the old names, and they appear to have removed the old names in the newest version of the fido2 library (currently 1.0.0). 

This causes errors when using "make init" or trying to run the solo1 cli after installing it with pip3, as it will get the latest version of the fido2 library and crash with the following error:

    ImportError: cannot import name 'CTAP1' from 'fido2.ctap1' ([...]/solo1-cli/venv/lib/python3.10/site-packages/fido2/ctap1.py)

Pinning the fido2 package to version 0.9.2 fixes the crash, but probably the solo1-cli code should be updated to match the most recent (and hopefully stable) API of the fido2 library.
